      <bioghist id="aspace_b16da2ff22a35fbbcbdc2bf0ddc1bf4b">
         <head>Archibald John Wilson</head>
         <p>Archibald John Wilson was born on December 26, 1923 in Scranton, Pennsylvania. Wilson enlisted in the Army in 1943 and served in Europe and the south Pacific. After being discharged, he attended Columbia University and spent most of his working life with Bank of America.</p>
         <p>Wilson was an active contributor to the gay liberation movement in San Francisco and the Bay Area and was also active in advocating for the rights of gay Veterans. He was an early member and commander of the Alexander Hamilton Post 448 of the American Legion, a predominately LGBT American Legion Post.</p>
         <p>Archibald John Wilson died on July 6, 2011.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <prefercite id="aspace_3e3743d4ed144402a572448532ce5cb3">
